article.description: Chris Clemmings scored 17 points, Devontae Cacoc added 15 points and nine rebounds, and UNC Wilmington had its second best shooting performance in a 100-64 blowout win over Radford on Saturday.
article.headline: Cacoc's hot shooting helps UNC Wilmington top Radford 100-64
article.linkText: Cacoc's hot shooting helps UNC Wilmington top Radford 100-64
article.story: WILMINGTON, N.C. -- Chris Clemmings scored 17 points, Devontae Cacoc added 15 points and nine rebounds, and UNC Wilmington had its second best shooting performance in a 100-64 blowout win over Radford on Saturday. Cacok's 7-for-7 performance, combined with an 8-for-8 mark in a 96-75 win over Campbell on Wednesday, gives him a school-record 15 consecutive field goals over the last two games. Ambrose Mosley, who made three 3s and finished with 11 points, turned a steal into a fast-break layup to give UNC Wilmington an 11-2 lead just over two minutes into the game, and the Seahawks extended their lead to 29-9 midway through the half. Mosley and company forced 15 first-half turnovers and scored 34 points off turnovers for the game. The Seahawks (10-1) shot 67 percent from the field en route to their seventh straight win and fourth overall scoring at least 100 points. Ed Polite Jr. had 20 points on 9-of-12 shooting and 13 boards for Radford (4-6).
